EXTRACTED VALUE: The barman places a vodka and tonic in front of me and gives me a quizzical look. “Cheer up!” he says. “It can’t be that bad!”
Win motioned to the house. Terese stood there, watching them silently. "Then say good-bye to La Derrière and let's be on our way."
“That’s how babies feel,” said Keith. “Apparently. They think: I am nothing and I should be everything.”
